description: As much as Dravid tries to brush it off, the discussions around India's loss in the World Test Championship final and the ODI World Cup final keep cropping up. Asked whether India will manage to cross the line this time, Dravid smiled.
title: We have moved on from our defeat in Ahmedabad: Rahul Dravid

description: South Africa, a former semi-finalist, faces India in the T20 World Cup final after defeating Bangladesh by three wickets. The match at Kensington Oval is set to be a high-stakes battle for the championship title, showcasing top talent from both teams. Expect an intense and thrilling showdown as the cricketing giants compete for victory.
title: IND vs SA T20 World Cup Final: Key facts and match details

description: Tamil Nadu Chief Minister MK Stalin wrote to Prime Minister Narendra Modi on Friday, requesting an exemption for the state from conducting the NEET for admissions to medical colleges. Stalin emphasized that the selection process for professional courses should be through class 12 marks to alleviate the stress students face. In his letter to PM Modi, Stalin explained that this change would help lift off unwarranted additional stress that students face. Stalin's request comes amid a nationwide uproar over NEET paper leak cases.
title: MK Stalin writes to PM Modi, 8 CMs to abolish NEET nationally

description: Amidst infrastructure challenges, the recurring waterlogging issues at key locations like the Minto Road underpass and Pragati Maidan transit corridor call for urgent and effective solutions to prevent disruptions and ensure public safety.
title: Rain of terror: No light at tunnel end as usual suspects submerge again

description: India and South Africa are set to face off in the T20 World Cup final, with rain expected to significantly affect the outcome. Both teams have been unbeaten in the tournament, with India overpowering England in a rain-delayed semifinal and South Africa reaching their first-ever World Cup final.
title: India vs SA: Will rain overshadow T20 World Cup final?

description: Union civil aviation minister Ram Mohan Naidu announced on Saturday that a war room has been set up to ensure refunds or alternate flights for passengers affected by the Delhi airport canopy collapse incident. This incident occurred on Friday at the Delhi Airport Terminal 1. Naidu also expressed condolences for the loss of life in the incident. "The minister assured that proactive measures are being taken to ensure such incidents are not repeated." He said passengers would get a guaranteed refund within seven days.
title: Airport collapse: Aviation minister says war room on duty for refunds

description: South Africa have lived with the 'chokers' tag for a very long time and Rohit Sharma's India would surely hate such a tag with all their heart. Since the 2013 Champions Trophy, success in ICC events has kept eluding India even as they have come agonizingly close time and time again.
title: T20 WC final: India aim to end title drought, SA seek to bury 'chokers' tag

description: Fatal cases of amoebic meningoencephalitis in Malabar districts linked to water activities. Health officials recommend caution during swimming to prevent infections from Vermamoeba vermiformis and other amoebas.
title: Another child tests positive for rare brain infection in Malappuram

description: Nasa astronauts Butch Wilmore and Sunita Williams, aboard Boeing's Starliner, remain at the ISS as engineers address thruster and helium leak issues. Nasa's Steve Stich assures their safety and no rush to return. Ground tests are planned. Despite challenges, the astronauts are assisting ISS operations, and provisions are sufficient for an extended stay.
title: 'Not stranded': Butch Wilmore, Sunita Williams 'enjoying their time' at space station

description: RSS chief Mohan Bhagwat met with Reliance chairman Mukesh Ambani at his residence, Antilia, in Mumbai. The meeting took place as the Ambani family prepares for Anant Ambani's grand wedding. Bhagwat reportedly joined the Ambani family for dinner during his visit. Earlier in the day, Bhagwat attended a book launch event celebrating legendary singer Asha Bhosle, who turned 90 last September. The RSS chief recently made the headlines after he advised the government to prioritise the crisis that has engulfed Manipur.
title: RSS chief Bhagwat visits Ambani family at Antilia for dinner

description: Under mounting pressure, the search for me reaches Kancheepuram, where the authorities draw closer. The imminent need to surrender and face the truth looms large, signaling a potential resolution to the twisted saga of mistaken identity and elusive justice.
title: Impersonating TN man fools police, courts, wife for two decades

description: In Isnapur, Vishal's family faced a heartbreaking loss when he was fatally attacked by stray dogs. With plans to send Vishal to school, the migrant labourer couple now grapples with the tragedy, leaving the community in mourning over the string of recent dog attacks.
title: Pack of strays maul 6-year-old boy to death in Telangana

description: Scam artist Afsan Parveen used dating apps like Tinder to lure men to cafes for extortion. Her arrest followed an extortion case filed by a victim, revealing a widespread scam involving cafe and bar owners targeting tourists in various countries.
title: Right swipe for wrong reason: Dates fleeced of lakhs at cafes

description: To avoid upcoming price increases by Jio and Airtel, customers should schedule prepaid recharges before July 3. Jio allows up to 50 recharges to be queued, offering savings on long-term plans. Postpaid users may consider switching to lower plans if data usage allows to manage the hike.

description: Virat Kohli has been dismissed without scoring twice in his worst-ever appearance in six T20 World Cups. India are aiming to end their 11-year trophy drought in global cricket competitions. South Africa are chasing their first men's World Cup title in any limited-overs format.
title: 'Like Dhoni...': Kaif feels Virat Kohli can become a hero

description: Reliance Jio and Airtel revise mobile tariff plans, increasing unlimited 5G data costs. Jio users must pay Rs 110 extra. Airtel offers unlimited 5G data starting at Rs 239 for Prepaid customers. To maintain benefits, recharges are necessary. Certain prepaid packs are ineligible for Airtel's unlimited 5G Data benefits.
title: 5G prices up for Jio users, company increases min price of ‘unlimited 5G plans’

description: Enhance your iPhone calling experience with live voicemail feature setup, custom greetings, and efficient message management. Optimize communication by sending calls to voicemail, accessing transcripts, and utilizing call back options for seamless interactions.

description: TRAI's new MNP policy enhances security by introducing a waiting period for UPC allocation to prevent fraudulent SIM swap techniques, ensuring user data protection and maintaining a seamless MNP process for telecom service users.

description: Chris Gayle's endorsement of Virat Kohli's capabilities, despite his recent struggle, sets the stage for an intense T20 World Cup final between India and South Africa at Kensington Oval. Kohli's past successes and current challenges add layers of anticipation to the upcoming match.
title: 'We know how dominant...': Gayle backs Kohli ahead of T20 WC final

description: The recent monsoon in Delhi brought unprecedented rainfall, leading to traffic disruptions, tragic incidents, and flight delays. Despite challenges, the city's air quality remained satisfactory, with predictions of continued heavy rain prompting an orange alert. The event highlighted the impact of extreme weather on daily life in the capital.

description: Following the canopy collapse at IGI Airport, hospital assistance, passenger support, and extrication efforts played vital roles in the response to the incident. The injured were provided medical aid, passengers received assistance, and rescue teams worked on freeing trapped individuals.
title: Airport roof collapse flattens cars, kills cabbie; lucky escape for others

description: In Manchipppa thanda, Nizamabad, Mahesh's wife abused him on June 23. He reported the incident on Thursday, resulting in her being booked by the police.
title: Man comes home drunk, wife brands him with burning wood

description: Individuals like Virma Ram Jaat have been instrumental in supporting candidates from tribal areas like Banswara to secure teaching positions through dummy candidate assistance. The success of these candidates is attributed to the reservation quotas for ST and SC individuals in district level recruitment exams within the Tribal Sub Plan (TSP) areas.
title: Failed govt job aspirants in Rajasthan turn dummy candidates
